##Normal Distribution bootstrap code to illustrate central limit theorom
## Get sample for normal distribution
Normsample <- rnorm(n, 100, 5)
sdNormSample <- sd(Normsample)

## Print random sample summary results 
cat("Random sample summary :\n")
## Random sample summary :
print(summary(Normsample))
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   91.13   96.22  101.20  100.50  103.90  111.20
cat("Random sample SD :\n")
## Random sample SD :
print(sdNormSample)
## [1] 5.071687
hist(Normsample,xlab = "Random Normal Sample")

##First Sample size -100
## Initialize bootstrap mean vector as numeric type of size 100
bootmeanVector100 <- numeric(100)

## Run bootstrap sequence on Normsample and save bootsample means to bootmean vector
for (i in 1:100){
  bootStrapSample <- sample(Normsample, size = length(Normsample), replace = TRUE)
  bootmeanVector100[i] <- mean(bootStrapSample)
}

## Print bootstrap mean summary results to screen
cat("Bootstrap sample's summary statistics:\n")
## Bootstrap sample's summary statistics:
print(summary(bootmeanVector100))
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   99.17  100.10  100.40  100.50  100.80  102.60
sdbootmeanVector100 <- sd(bootmeanVector100)
cat("Bootstrap sample's SD:\n")
## Bootstrap sample's SD:
print(sdbootmeanVector100)
## [1] 0.6637748
hist(bootmeanVector100,xlab = "Bootstrapped random sample of size 100")

##Second Sample size -1000
## Initialize bootstrap mean vector as numeric type of size 1000
bootmeanVector1000 <- numeric(1000)

## Run bootstrap sequence on Normsample and save bootsample means to bootmean vector
for (i in 1:1000){
  bootStrapSample <- sample(Normsample, size = length(Normsample), replace = TRUE)
  bootmeanVector1000[i] <- mean(bootStrapSample)
}

## Print bootstrap mean summary results to screen
cat("Bootstrap sample's summary statistics:\n")

##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   98.12  100.00  100.50  100.50  101.00  103.40
sdbootmeanVector1000 <- sd(bootmeanVector1000)
cat("Bootstrap sample's SD:\n")
## Bootstrap sample's SD:
print(sdbootmeanVector1000)
## [1] 0.7016741
hist(bootmeanVector1000,xlab = "Bootstrapped random sample of size 1000")

##Exponential Distribution bootstrap code to illustrate central limit theorom
## Get sample for normal distribution
Expsample <- rexp(n)

## Print random sample summary results 
cat("Random Exp sample summary :\n")
## Random Exp sample summary :
print(summary(Expsample))
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## 0.03913 0.29410 0.65600 0.94010 1.21700 5.59300
sdExpsample <- sd(Expsample)
cat("Random Exp Sample SD:\n")
## Random Exp Sample SD:
print(sdExpsample)
## [1] 1.026112
hist(Expsample,xlab = "ExponentialRandomSample")

##First Sample size -100
## Initialize bootstrap mean vector as numeric type of size 100
bootmeanVectorExp100 <- numeric(100)

## Run bootstrap sequence on Normsample and save bootsample means to bootmean vector
for (i in 1:100){
  bootStrapExpSample <- sample(Expsample, size = length(Expsample), replace = TRUE)
  bootmeanVectorExp100[i] <- mean(bootStrapExpSample)
}

## Print bootstrap mean summary results to screen
cat("Bootstrap sample's summary statistics:\n")
## Bootstrap sample's summary statistics:
print(summary(bootmeanVectorExp100))
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##  0.6794  0.8583  0.9551  0.9585  1.0560  1.3550
sdbootmeanVectorExp100 <- sd(bootmeanVectorExp100)
cat("sdbootmeanVectorExp100 Boot Sample SD:\n")
## sdbootmeanVectorExp100 Boot Sample SD:
print(sdbootmeanVectorExp100)
## [1] 0.1380199
hist(bootmeanVectorExp100,xlab = "Bootstrapped EXP sample of size 100")
